even cultural traction across a century in which composers were still first and foremost performers.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aMusic printingxHistoryy16th century. 0aMusic publishingxHistoryy16th century. 0aMusicy16th centuryxHistory and criticism. 7aMUSIC / Genres & Styles / Classical.2bisacsh  a16th century.  aart.  aartists.  abeauty.  aclassical music.  acomposers.  acultural history.  adance.  aengaging.  afamous composers.  ahistory of music.  amusic history.  amusic printing.  anobility.  apage turner.  apaintings.  aperformance scripts.  aperformers.  aperforming arts.  apolyphony.  apublishing sacred music.  arenaissance period.  aretrospective.  aromance.  aromantic.  aroyalty.  awestern music.  awriters.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052027650540uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052095711440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520957114423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520957114/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY